<div class="row"><hr class="line" />
<h3>Some retouching techniques and effects you may consider include:</h3>
<ul>
<li>If the scan is crooked, rotating the image to properly align it.</li>
<li>Retouch the image to remove any scratches, dust, damage, etc.</li>
<li>Retouch the image to remove any visually distracting elements.</li>
<li>Crop the image as necessary and correct any odd edges.</li>
<li>Use the healing brush, clone stamp tool, patch tool, etc.</li>
<li>Adjust any levels, hue, saturation, and any other adjustments that may be necessary by using adjustment layers.</li>
<li>Convert to grayscale if necessary.</li>
<li>Convert to a monochrome sepia or yellowed print by using an adjustment layer.</li>
<li>Burn/dodge shadows &amp; highlights to bring out details or aesthetics in the image.</li>
</ul>
</div>
